>Yep, that is the scenario that makes the most sense.
>
>Christmas music is not the great seller that is was 20+ years 
>ago.  This city has become much more diverse racially/ethnically, 
>then add the fact that at least one major radio station will go 'all 
>Christmas" beginning the Friday before thanksgiving and you can see 
>the main reasons for the loss of interest.
>
>The way it plays out: After an initial spurt of interest when the 
>music is put in (50-75 titles) it goes down and picks up again a few 
>days before Christmas.
>
>Then in typical American style, right after the 25th, interest dies 
>off almost completely and the music is essentially deadwood.
>
>It's really a lot of work for little added return, but it adds to 
>the fun of the season.
>
>Rob
>
>
